The Stone Fountain~
   You stand in a huge chamber built from huge blocks of gray stone.  Five
pillars stand in a line on both the east and west sides of the room, holding up
a giant flat ceiling that lofts high overhead.  In each of the four corners of
the room sits an enormous stone sconce, casting light and shadows throughout
the room.  The feeling of age and serenity that radiates from the vast chamber
is only increased by the vacant simplicity, making this large room feel more
like a place of respect than one of fear or foreboding.  The stillness is
disturbed occasionally by a gentle current of air, dancing off the distant sea.
There are exits in each direction.    
