#1502
A Shrine to the Shadows~
   Utter silence is one thing immediately noticed upon entering this dark
shrine carved into the solid rock of the cliffs surrounding the island.  
Lacking the well-lit ambience of the rest of the guildhall, the shrine is lit
dimly with purple candles placed at even intervals around the room that
illuminate the vaulted ceiling irregularly, making shadows dance and play at
the bare edges of perception, forming figures almost solid before dissipating
into nothingness once again.  Against the far wall is an altar stone of black
marble with a single blue taper burning steadily, always keeping the room
between the realms of light and darkness.  Glinting against the walls of the
shrine are marvelous mosaics set with lapis, amethyst, dark sapphire, and rare
purple corundum.  The only exit is south through a short hallway back to the
stone fountain.    
~
